# Keep the docker build context small. These are either heavy/ephemeral or
# provided at runtime via the compose bind-mount (./:/app), so excluding them from
# the build context does not affect the in-repo `docker compose` image build
# (which only COPYs .go-version, core/go.mod, core/go.sum, scripts/install-tools.sh)
# nor the runtime mount. The devkit builder (Dockerfile.devkit) re-creates bin/ and
# core/plugin.so itself, and statically links the committed Devkit theme system
# plugin re-included below.
.git
.tmp
output
node_modules
**/node_modules
data
# Re-include the committed Devkit theme system plugin so the devkit builder's
# `COPY . .` carries it (sysplugin-prepare statically links it into core/plugin.so).
# Everything else under data/ stays excluded. The Developer plugin is intentionally
# NOT re-included: it is local-dev-only and excluded from the devkit distribution
# (make-devkit.sh also stashes it out of the build).
!data/plugins/system/com.flarego.devkit
plugins
bin
*.so
